      <preamble>
         <p>The Scottish Ministers make the following Order in exercise of the powers conferred by section 59(6)(a) of the Criminal Proceedings etc. (Reform) (Scotland) Act 2007<noteRef href="#f00001" class="footnote" marker="1"/> and all other powers enabling them to do so.</p>
         <p>In accordance with section 59(7B) of that Act, the Scottish Ministers have had regard to a proposal of the Scottish Courts and Tribunals Service for the making of this Order.</p>
         <p>In accordance with section 59(7C) of that Act, the Lord President and the Scottish Courts and Tribunals Service have given consent to the making of the Order.</p>
         <formula name="enactingText">
            <p>In accordance with section 81(3)(a) of that Act, a draft of this instrument has been laid before, and approved by resolution of, the Scottish Parliament.</p>
         </formula>
      </preamble>
      <body>
         <article eId="article-1">
            <heading>Citation and commencement</heading>
            <num>1.</num>
            <content>
               <p>This Order may be cited as the Justice of the Peace Courts (Sheriffdom of South Strathclyde, Dumfries and Galloway) etc. Amendment Order 2019 and comes into force on 8 June 2019.</p>
            </content>
         </article>
         <article eId="article-2">
            <heading>Relocation of the justice of the peace court for the sheriff court district of Airdrie</heading>
            <num>2.</num>
            <content>
               <p>In column 2 of schedule 1 (establishment of justice of the peace courts) of the Justice of the Peace Courts (Sheriffdom of South Strathclyde, Dumfries and Galloway) etc. Order 2009<noteRef href="#f00002" class="footnote" marker="2"/>, for “Coatbridge” substitute “Airdrie”.</p>
            </content>
         </article>
